      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ROWEINER'S DANCE (4) was well in commission last start over 900m at Innisfail when sixth. Distance specialist with 14 wins and five minor placings from 25 runs and is expected to be in the finish. NORTHERN PRIDE (3) is back after a break of four months. Started the last campaign in good style when in the placings over 1100m at Mackay. Looks a strong prospect. VIBURNUM (5) comes here off a last-start fourth, only beaten 0.7 lengths, over 1100m at Julia Creek. Has a good record at this journey and is a hope. RUBY CHICKS (6) was safely held when resuming over 1000m at Townsville, finishing ninth and beaten 4.5 lengths. Is a second up winner in the past and can give this a shake.",
